io.lettuce.core.cluster.pubsub.api.async

Interface RedisClusterPubSubAsyncCommands<K,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - Key type.
    V - Value type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    BaseRedisAsyncCommands<K,V>, RedisAsyncCommands<K,V>, RedisClusterAsyncCommands<K,V>, RedisGeoAsyncCommands<K,V>, RedisHashAsyncCommands<K,V>, RedisHLLAsyncCommands<K,V>, RedisKeyAsyncCommands<K,V>, RedisListAsyncCommands<K,V>, RedisPubSubAsyncCommands<K,V>, RedisScriptingAsyncCommands<K,V>, RedisServerAsyncCommands<K,V>, RedisSetAsyncCommands<K,V>, RedisSortedSetAsyncCommands<K,V>, RedisStreamAsyncCommands<K,V>, RedisStringAsyncCommands<K,V>, RedisTransactionalAsyncCommands<K,V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    RedisClusterPubSubAsyncCommandsImpl

    public interface RedisClusterPubSubAsyncCommands<K,V>
extends RedisPubSubAsyncCommands<K,V>
    Asynchronous and thread-safe Redis Cluster PubSub API. Operations are executed either on the main connection or a PubSubAsyncNodeSelection.
    Since:
    4.4
    Author:
    Mark Paluch
